[Marek] Boost bug in OpenTissue (reported by Ulrik Bonde 2. Maj 2017)
	OpenTissue/core/math/math_random.h uses BOOST_VERSION to detected if boost random should be used. However, using 1.61.0 on Linux, causes failures. First time is not a member of std (missing ctime include?), second details are not found (should be math::detail?). However this does not completely fix the bug???
	Error is not reproducable on Apple using Clang 8.X somehow the compiler acts like BOOST_VERSION is not defined.

