[MAREK] Make Debug Render: Introduce two parameters
	debug_render = on
	debug_render_level = 0     # Number determines the neighborhood side, number of times to call star recursively on the region that one is doing a mesh operation on
Inside do_optimization before an operation is done we call the function
       do_debug_rendering(….)
If debug_rendring is on. This function should make a “debug.svg” file of how the mesh looks like before the operation is tried out. The function takes the simplex_set and the simplex the operation is supposed to work on as argument as well as the mesh and debug render level. In the debug.svg file the mesh feature that is worked on should be highlighed (draw differently from the rest of the mesh). The idea is to overwrite the debug.svg file in for each operation and only render a small neighborhood of where the mesh operation is happening.

